To "hang" or wait around a location, preferably without drawing attention to oneself.

An individual may lurk in person ("''He lurked unseen in the trees, watching the mourning family''") or through the internet.

An internet [[lurker]] is an individual who visits a web-based forum (chat-room, messageboard, etc) to read the entries without posting any of their own or registering their presence.

